Potentilla gracilis is a species of flowering plant in the rose family Rosaceae. 
It is commonly known as the slender cinquefoil due to its thin and delicate stems. 
The leaves are pinnately compound, with small green leaflets and a silky texture. 
The flowers are bright yellow and have five petals, with a prominent center of stamens. 
Potentilla gracilis can be found growing in meadows, rocky slopes, and alpine habitats. 
It is native to North America and can be found from Alaska to California. 
This plant is valued for its ornamental beauty and is often used in landscaping and gardening projects.
